211
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:58,240
you've forgotten them all?

212
00:18:59,359 --> 00:19:00,400
Unpleasant?

213
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,319
Sorry.

214
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,680
I really have forgotten a lot.

215
00:19:14,799 --> 00:19:15,720
It's actually not so bad.

216
00:19:16,240 --> 00:19:18,200
Many people try hard to forget things,

217
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:20,480
but you forgot because of the accident.

218
00:19:21,039 --> 00:19:23,279
I guess it's a blessing in disguise.

219
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:27,000
So, the unpleasantness you mentioned,

220
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:29,119
were you referring to something specific?

221
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:33,440
No, I just meant unpleasantness in general.

222
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:36,680
In married life, between husband and wife,

223
00:19:36,839 --> 00:19:38,359
it's normal to have some friction.

224
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:58,279
Come on.

225
00:19:59,559 --> 00:20:00,279
Keep drawing.

226
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:09,599
Xiao Tangyuan's condition has greatly improved.

227
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:13,440
Thank you.

228
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,039
You give the children free sessions every week.

229
00:20:15,039 --> 00:20:15,880
You provide psychological therapy.

230
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:16,799
They really like you.

231
00:20:17,039 --> 00:20:17,759
You're welcome.

232
00:20:18,359 --> 00:20:20,279
Being able to use what I've learned

233
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,519
to help these children

234
00:20:21,839 --> 00:20:22,799
feels very meaningful to me.

235
00:20:23,839 --> 00:20:25,880
Mr. Yuan is very caring.

236
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,640
He looks after so many children every day.

237
00:20:27,839 --> 00:20:28,759
It's really hard work.

238
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,200
It's just physical labor.

239
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,720
Mr. Yuan seems to know a lot about psychology.

240
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,079
He has deep expertise as well.

241
00:20:40,559 --> 00:20:41,880
You're not an ordinary caregiver.

242
00:20:43,119 --> 00:20:44,440
Taking care of so many children at the welfare center

243
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,359
and doing it so well

244
00:20:45,759 --> 00:20:47,200
is no easy task.

245
00:20:50,799 --> 00:20:52,160
So I started looking into Mr. Yuan.

246
00:20:52,359 --> 00:20:53,519
I did some research.

247
00:20:54,799 --> 00:20:56,079
I found out that Mr. Yuan

248
00:20:56,079 --> 00:20:57,559
was once half a colleague of mine.

249
00:20:58,279 --> 00:20:59,440
But why is he now

250
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,559
just a regular caregiver?

251
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:06,839
Mr. Yuan, please don't misunderstand.

252
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,519
I'm just curious.

253
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,240
Maybe Mr. Yuan

254
00:21:10,799 --> 00:21:12,440
has secrets he can't talk about.

255
00:21:20,119 --> 00:21:20,920
Xiao Tangyuan.

256
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,279
Let's go.

257
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,160
Come on.

258
00:22:22,359 --> 00:22:24,400
So after the accident,

259
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,279
you really forgot a lot of things.

260
00:22:28,359 --> 00:22:30,039
My recent memories are a bit blurry.

261
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:33,359
But I remember earlier memories more clearly.

262
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,680
Sometimes I wonder,

263
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:40,519
if I hadn't met him back then,

264
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:43,240
what would things be like now?

265
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:44,880
Who knows?

266
00:22:45,279 --> 00:22:48,000
Maybe we’d still be pursuing dance together.

267
00:22:48,759 --> 00:22:50,680
Maybe working at some training center,

268
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:51,960
teaching kids.

269
00:23:02,279 --> 00:23:03,200
Hey, Lu Ming.

270
00:23:16,559 --> 00:23:17,440
Where is this?

271
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,400
Weren’t you coming to see Professor Zhong?

272
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:23,640
I asked classmates who still keep in touch with him.

273
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:24,799
He lives here.

274
00:23:30,279 --> 00:23:32,440
Isn’t Professor Zhong’s home in Building Four?

275
00:23:32,799 --> 00:23:33,799
What are you talking about?

276
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:35,559
Let’s go.

277
00:24:05,759 --> 00:24:06,559
Lu Ming

278
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:08,359
Come in

279
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:40,960
Have a seat.

280
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,000
Okay.

281
00:24:44,839 --> 00:24:47,920
Lu Ming, even though I'm just an adjunct teacher,

282
00:24:48,079 --> 00:24:49,240
I didn't teach you many classes.

283
00:24:49,599 --> 00:24:52,440
But you've always left a deep impression on me.

